    "en": {
      "title": "The atmosphere is formed to rain in four provinces",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Department of Meteorology says that in the next few days favorable atmospheric conditions are being created for thunderstorms in the evening in Uva, Eastern, North Central and Northern provinces.",
        "The EMA Department states that there will be several periods of rain in Western, Sabaragamuwa and North-Western provinces and in Kandy, Nuwara Eliya, Galle and Matara districts today. It is seen in the announcement issued by the Department of Meteorology this morning that rain or thundershowers will occur in other areas in the evening or at night.",
        "It is also stated in the announcement that heavy rainfall of more than 75 mm may occur in some places in Uruwa, Eastern, North Central and Northern provinces.",
        "As the sun is moving towards the south, the sun will reach the top of Manniyakulam, Ariviyal and Valayanmadam today at 12.11pm, the Department of Tourism further says."
      ],
